<h2 id="pagination" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#pagination"><span>Pagination</span></a></h2>
<p>Pagination means splitting a large collection of data into smaller pages.</p>
<p>Instead of returning all users at once: <code v-pre>GET /api/users</code>, you return a small part of the result: <code v-pre>GET /api/users?page=0&amp;size=20</code>. This means: give me page 0 with 20 users per page.</p>
<p>Pagination is very common in REST APIs because returning thousands or millions of records at once is slow, expensive, and bad for user experience.</p>
<p><strong>Spring Data uses zero-based page numbers by default.</strong></p>
<h3 id="pagination-styles" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#pagination-styles"><span>Pagination Styles</span></a></h3>
<ul>
<li>Page-Size</li>
<li>Limit-Offset</li>
<li>Cursor</li>
<li>Keyset</li>
</ul>
