<h2 id="cors" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#cors"><span>CORS</span></a></h2>
<p>CORS stands for: Cross-Origin Resource Sharing. It matters when your frontend and backend run on different origins.</p>
<h2 id="api-versioning" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#api-versioning"><span>API Versioning</span></a></h2>
<p>APIs change over time. Versioning helps avoid breaking old clients.</p>
<p>Common style:</p>
<ul>
<li>/api/v1/users</li>
<li>/api/v2/users</li>
</ul>
